
	String formatting:
	
	1) Capitalizes first non-tag string character of strings or dot terminated phrases
	2) Adds space after dot in not the first phrase
	3) Removes double space
	4) Leaves abbreviations as they are
	5) Truncates to number of fitting characters and tries to round up on space
	6) Adds an optional string or ' ...' (to the last open fitting tag) when the string has been truncated


